Package: w3m-ssl
Version: 0.5.1
Revision: 1
Description: Pager/text-based WWW browser with tables/frames support
License: OSI-Approved
Maintainer: Christian Swinehart <cswinehart@users.sourceforge.net>
BuildDepends: gc-static, openssl-dev, ncurses-dev, gettext-dev, gettext-bin, libiconv-dev
Depends: openssl-shlibs, ncurses-shlibs, launch, gettext, libiconv
Conflicts: w3m
Replaces: w3m
Source: mirror:sourceforge:w3m/w3m-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 0678b72e07e69c41709d71ef0fe5da13
ConfigureParams: --with-ssl=%p --with-termlib=ncurses --disable-image --with-imagelib=no --mandir=%p/share/man --libexecdir=%p/lib --with-editor=%p/bin/editor --with-browser=%p/bin/launch --disable-w3mmailer --with-mailer='%p/bin/launch -l'
GCC: 3.3
CompileScript: <<
 ./configure %c
 make
<<
InstallScript: <<
 make install DESTDIR=%d
 mkdir -p %i/share/man/man1
 install -c -m 644 doc/w3m.1 %i/share/man/man1/
 mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n/english
 install -m 644 doc/* %i/share/doc/%n/english/
 mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n/japanese
 install -m 644 doc-jp/* %i/share/doc/%n/japanese
 mkdir -p %i/share/%n/
 mv Bonus %i/share/%n/
<<
DocFiles: README TODO ChangeLog
Homepage: http://w3m.sourceforge.net
DescDetail: <<
 w3m is a text-based World Wide Web browser with IPv6 support. 
 It features excellent support for tables and frames. It can be 
 used as a standalone file pager, too.
<<
